// What Fe brings that Solidity can't:
//
// 1. TYPE SAFETY: Fp + Fp uses addmod automatically. Can't forget the modulus.
//
// 2. CONST GENERICS: Poseidon<T=3, RF=8, RP=57> parameterizes the
//    permutation width and round counts. One codebase, many configurations.
//
// 3. CONST FN: Round constants generated at compile time from the
//    field parameters. No JavaScript codegen. No hardcoded tables.
//
// 4. OPERATOR OVERLOADING: `state[i].pow5() + Fp::new(C[rc])` reads
//    like the math paper, not like assembly.
//
// 5. INLINE TESTS: #[test] right next to the code, verified by `fe test`.
//    No separate test harness.
